1. User Registration (Sign Up)
Email + password signup
Optional: phone number signup
Validation (strong password rules)
Duplicate account prevention

2. Login (Authentication)
Email/username + password
Token-based auth (JWT or session)
Remember me (optional)

3. Token Management
Access token (short-lived)
Refresh token (long-lived)
Token rotation
Token revocation (logout)

4. Logout
Invalidate tokens
Logout from:
Current device
All devices (important scenario)

5. Email Verification
Send verification email
Verify account before access
Resend verification link

6. Password Management
Forgot password (reset flow)
Reset token expiry
Change password (when logged in)

7. Account Security
Rate limiting (prevent brute force)
Account lock after multiple failed logins
CAPTCHA (optional but realistic)

8. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
Roles (admin, user, etc.)
Permissions
Route protection

9. Multi-Device / Session Management
Track active sessions
Ability to:
View logged-in devices
Revoke specific sessions

10. OAuth / Social Login (Optional but strong)
Google login
GitHub login

👉 This is a strong senior-level addition.

🔐 Advanced / Senior-Level Scenarios
11. Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
OTP via email/SMS
Authenticator apps (e.g. Google Authenticator)
12. Audit & Logging
Login attempts
Password changes
Suspicious activity
13. Account Deactivation / Deletion
Soft delete
Hard delete (GDPR-style thinking)
14. API Security
Rate limiting per user/IP
API key support (for integrations)
15. Multi-Tenant Support (VERY senior)
Users belong to organizations
Same email can exist in different orgs